                    {
                        "comments": [],
                        "name": "Data transformation",
                        "protocolType": {
                            "comments": [],
                            "annotationValue": "Data transformation",
                            "termSource": null,
                            "termAccession": ""
                        },
                        "description": "<p>After the mass spectrometry detection is completed, the raw data of LC-MS is preprocessed by&nbsp;Progenesis QI (Waters Corporation, Milford, USA) software, and a 3D data matrix in CSV format is exported. The information in this 3D matrix includes: sample information, metabolite name and mass spectral response intensity. Internal standard peaks, as well as any known false positive peaks (including noise, column bleed and derivatized reagent peaks), were removed from the data matrix, deredundant and peak pooled.</p>",
